<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1005,1292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
This species was described based on a single female specimen collected by Adan Rivera on 
<date pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1948-02-09">February 9, 1948</date>
, at Zamorano, 
<collectingCountry box="[428,546,1048,1074]" name="Honduras" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Honduras</collectingCountry>
. Rivera and G. Cisneros were probably collectors who helped Cockerell during his stay in 
<collectingCountry box="[418,532,1092,1118]" name="Honduras" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Honduras</collectingCountry>
(Jesus Orozco, pers. com.). The 
<typeStatus box="[946,1049,1092,1118]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[1070,1145,1092,1118]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1466,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1398,1466,1921]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Centris adani Cockerell, 1949, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534186). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722956/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) is currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[221,311,1136,1162]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
under the number 58878 and has the following data label: 192 [handwritten]\ Zamorano 
<collectingCountry box="[189,303,1179,1205]" name="Honduras" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Honduras</collectingCountry>
Feb.9. [handwritten] Arivera [?]\ 
